Let me start by saying I don’t know how this place doesn’t have 5 stars. I’d give it 15 if I could.  I discovered this place a little over a year ago, and it is hands down my favorite restaurant in New York. The blend of food on the menu is absolutely dynamite. Oysters, clams, shrimp? Perfection. Feeling a lobster slider? They got it. Mussels in white wine with some garlic? YUP. Or my personal favorite, the Kittery burger. It is (and I don’t say this lightly) one of the best burgers I’ve ever had. Thick, plump, and juicy. It looks so good I think Spongebob based the Krabby Patty from Kitterys burger. Order that with a side of Kittery fries (or tots, OR onion rings, yes they have their own style of these) and your taste buds will suddenly find themselves in heaven.  Did I mention how good their drinks are as well? Goodness gracious, don’t get me started. But alas, I will. A wide selection of various drinks from their takes on conventional Mojitos (so sweet, so delicious) to the latest Arnold Palmer twist with bourbon (hint: get with the burger).  Trust me when I say you will NOT go wrong eating here. You are guaranteed to come back, get sucked into their weekly deals (my favorite being their dollar oyster nights) and before you know it you’ll be hosting your wedding here. Do yourself a favor, check it out, bless your taste buds and go home feeling like you’re on cloud 9.

Kittery was amazing, the ambiance is nice and warm. It is a cute and cozy space. I love the small bar they have next to the restauraunt where you can purchase ice cream or cocktails, who could beat that.The drinks were just OK, they were strong but lacked flavor. I had a rum punch and I am used to it being a little sweet but it was bitter. My fiance had a pinapple frozen margarita and his also lacked flavor.  I guess if you don't like sweet drinks and just want to get straight to the point with the drink it will be ok for you.  So back to the bar, they have a bench and a few chairs in front of the outside bar where you can sit and have you drink or treat as you wait for your table . I gave this place 4 stars because the wait was horrendous, it was over an hour. It was a good thing we were able to sit at the bar but there were other folks standing and waiting for an extremely long time. Of course due to COVID they have restrictions on the number of people at the bar and restaraunt so I guess safety first.  They however, have plenty of tables outdoor. Some are on the sidewalk, which is fine because it does not seem to be a high traffic area and some are enclosed in a beautiful  gated outdoor area. Once we finally sat down to eat the food more then made up for the wait. We got the fried calamari for appetizers and it was fried to perfection, flavor in every bite yum lol. For entree I got the sea seared scallops and they were juicy, crispy and filled with flavor, it came with string beans and a cauliflower puree that was divine. It was just the right amount of food. My fiance had the seafood stew in a tomato sauce and I kid you not, I almost ate his whole plate as well. He had mussels, scallops and shrimps with toasted garlic bread and it was a party in my mouth, I was very satisfied.  The service was amazing once we sat down, the food came out quite quickly and our waitress was so sweet and efficient, I am sorry I can't remember her name.  They allow you to go inside to use the restroom, in which there are 2 and the place is super clean. They offer hand sanitizer all around and everyone is wearing mask and gloves. All around It was a great experience and we will for sure go back. They just should try to get the wait time down, my stomach was talking to me by the time I ate lol.

The Sheepshead Bay Italian fish houses have nothing on this place.  Oysters, clams and shrimp all a buck a piece with service like you were at a gourmet spot in Manhattan.  Really, this crew does a fine job.  Try the soups there as well.  The fried fish platter was awesome too.  We had friends at two other tables who ordered their meal twice!  Fish restaurants dont last long here.  This is one of the first of its kind that for me will be a staple for visiting guest.  With Jennifer as your hostess you wont be disappointed.  With this warm reception and good food you would be hard pressed to go any place else.
Love the vibe here and outdoor patio.
Great happy hour! Oysters are delicious! Wait staf is very friendly, but because it's busy it's a little slow.

The servers are not attentive.   Needed to repeatedly remind the waiter about our drinks.  It was not crowded so the lack of attention to customers was surprising. The food itself was mediocre and inconsistent.  Some dishes were over seasoned while others were under.
Love this place. Excellent food, great location.
Love this place! Great service, food and wine!

$15 bottomless mimosas at brunch, $4 drafts for happy hour, and fantastic seafood?  This gets 5 stars all day.  Salads can have lobster, crab, salmon, and shrimp added.  Old Bay seasoning wafts through the air of the plentiful outdoor seating.  Having been to Kittery, ME each summer, this place is stiff competition for the entire town.
Absolutely loved the lobster Mac n cheese.
Great burgers and the mac n cheese is amazing. Nice wine selection too

Came here for happy hour. Overall my wife and I were just kind of underwhelmed. The dollar shrimp for happy hour was a good deal, but the other food was pretty average. Service was nice, but slow. It's not bad here, but probably wouldn't be a place we return to.
Nice little neighborhood seafood joint. Great for late lunch/early dinner, outdoor area as well.
good size oysters, spacious place, kids friendly, not too crowded.
Outstanding food with such a perfect relaxed atmosphere and staff that went above and beyond to help us! Will definitely go back! And on a friday night it was not obnoxiously packed!
Food was just okay,  service was good.

Absolutely delicious, the lobster rolls here are great, and for my appetizer I had the crab dip, also amazing. Service was attentive and friendly. Definitely looking forward to my next visit to the Kittery :)

Don't go on a Friday night. The service was pleasant but unbearably slow and they didn't apologize once. Just had the worst night out in NYC in the two years I've been living here, truly terrible. Food is fine but completely over priced. Definitely the last time I'll come here. You just can't depend on it. Such a shame, but think it needs new management.
Oysters, beer, lobster rolls and you don't have to trek to Red Hook! This place is legit, and I'm happy it exists. The staff is great and the beer selection is decent.
I'd only been in for drinks. Appreciated it being one of the few places open on July 4th. The bartender was very friendly. Seemed like a very chill place to eat, or just have a drink.
Decent food, very slow, poor service. Wish we would have tried somewhere else.
Lots of seafood options, dollar oysters and outside seating in the front.
Perfect drinks for the summer
Dollar oysters and an adorable atmosphere. Can't be beaten.

We walked by on a beautiful sunny day and sat outside. I was expecting comfort / fried seafood (potentially) but we had two amazing salads (the brussel sprouts and burrata). The oysters were only $1 each and were delicious too. I will definitely return!
Staff was great... happy hour can't  be beat.
Good happy hour sliders and beer+!)
Nice vibe and good food. Easy local joint

I must say I am not really a seafood lover but after eating at Kittery of Brooklyn, I have to say I love seafood.  The Lobster was out of this world and the service was great.  The staff was warm and welcoming.  They helped me with my choice on the seafood as I was a bit scared to try it.  The food was delicious and I would definitely go back to eat there again.
Favorite restaurant in Carroll garden's, happy hour specials are unbeatable! The environment, staff and food are outstanding. Definitely recommend!
A gem in Carroll Gardens. You could never go wrong with dollar oysters. There is something to do here every night of the week.
Great place to go for brunch, service was excellent

The Kittery offers an intimate and familial atmosphere with delectable selections at a price that is more than reasonable for the quality of food. I'll be eating here more, and bringing my friends and family here. The bartender, Tyler, is amiable and made my stay here more pleasant.  The waiters are very attentive and the food is brought in a timely manner. Highly recommended.
I'm new to the neighborhood, and I never really was into seafood, but now whenever I see food all I want it the Kittery. The mussels and salmon was awesome! Deff recommend
Great service (Tyler is wicked awesome) Sit at the bar and get the $1 happy hour oysters, with the mussels for your meal.  So effin' amazing and at a great price too 💃🏾
Best seafood in Brooklyn!!!!!! Gotta check this spot out everyone
I really like this place.  Very accommodating staff!  I've been here for brunch and dinner.   Food is always delicious.  Plus bluepoint oysters for $1 M-F during happy hour!
Was actually surprised how good it was. My wife and I shared the crab dip and for dinner I had the fried seafood platter which we probably could have split, just an immense amount of food.
Solid. Great Bloody Mary at brunch. Clean spot w great service. Seafood is plentiful but plenty of other options. All done well.

The happy hour is always a great experience. Fresh delicious dollar oysters and great beers and wine selected for happy hour. Allison behind the bar always has a great vibe -- professional and friendly. After the management seemed  to struggle with the quality of their waitstaff and service on the floor in general  they seem to be getting their footing. Love sitting at the bar. (Wish they had a better brunch, though.)
More reasonably priced lobster roll than that of Red Hook Lobster Pound...and just as good, if not better!
Nice atmosphere and festive outdoor seating but little else not recommend here. Less than fresh and less then tasty. Save your money for a trip to Maine.
Bad clams=sick.   Lobster roll was safe and buttery.
